1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 20-A MRSA §1, sub-§13-A, ¶B-1, as enacted by PL 2003, c. 477, §2, is
3 amended by amending subparagraph (1) to read:
4 (1) Who is sharing the housing of other persons due to loss of housing or economic
5 hardship or a similar reason; is living in a motel, hotel, trailer park or camping
6 ground due to the lack of alternative adequate accommodation; is living in an
7 emergency or transitional shelter; or is abandoned in a hospital; or is awaiting
8 foster care placement;
9 Sec. 2. 20-A MRSA §1651, sub-§4, as enacted by PL 1981, c. 693, §§5 and 8, is
10 amended to read:
11 4. District school committee to act as district board of trustees. A community
12 school district may vote at any time on the article in section 1602, subsection 1, paragraph
13 C, to see determine if the district school committee shall be is authorized to perform the
14 function of the district board of trustees. If the municipalities vote affirmatively on that
15 article, the district school committee shall must perform the duties of the district board of
16 trustees under this chapter.
17 Sec. 3. 20-A MRSA §1653, sub-§1, ¶C, as amended by PL 1993, c. 668, §1, is
18 further amended to read:
19 C. Notwithstanding paragraphs A and B, the voters of a district may vote on an
20 appropriate article at meetings called by the municipal officers of the respective
21 member towns, in accordance with section 1602, to establish a fixed common date for
22 all newly elected school committee members to assume their terms of office. The
23 common date must be subsequent to the last annual municipal election within the
24 district, but may be no later than July 1st of the next fiscal year. The adoption of such
25 a common date is conditional upon the favorable passage of this article at each of the
26 meetings of the member towns. This paragraph does not apply to commencement of
27 terms of office of members elected to fill vacancies. Vacancies are filled for the
28 remainder of the unexpired term as provided in subsection 2, paragraph A.
29 Sec. 4. 20-A MRSA §1751-A is enacted to read:
30 §1751-A. Withdrawal from community school district
31 The residents of a participating municipality within a community school district may
32 petition and vote to withdraw from the district in the same manner as a participating
33 municipality within a regional school unit may petition to withdraw in accordance with
34 section 1466.
35 Sec. 5. 20-A MRSA §2951, sub-§2, as enacted by PL 1981, c. 693, §§5 and 8, is
36 repealed.
37 Sec. 6. 20-A MRSA §3804, as amended by PL 2019, c. 219, §3, is further amended
38 to read:
39 §3804. Audit
40 An education service center shall adhere to generally accepted accounting principles
41 and shall annually engage an external auditor to do an independent audit of the education
Page 1 - 132LR0131(01)

412 service center's finances. The education service center shall submit the audit to its members
423 and to the department. The audit must be conducted in the same manner as a school
434 administrative unit audit in accordance with chapter 221, subchapter 2. An education
445 service center under the fiscal authority of a school administrative unit may be included in
456 the audit of that school administrative unit and is not required to file an additional audit
467 under this section.
7 Sec. 7. 20-A MRSA §6051, sub-§4, as amended by PL 2007, c. 668, §32, is further
8 amended to read:
9 4. Initial report to commissioner. On or before November 1st, An initial report to
10 the commissioner must be included as part of the audit under subsection 1. In the report the
11 school board shall provide the commissioner with:
12 C. Written determination of whether or not proper budgetary controls are in place;
13 D. A written determination of whether or not the annual financial data submitted to
14 the department is correct, including submission of an audited reconciliation of the
15 annual financial data prepared and certified by the auditor; and
16 E. A written determination as to whether the school administrative unit has complied
17 with applicable provisions of the Essential Programs and Services Funding Act.
18 Sec. 8. 20-A MRSA c. 608, as amended, is repealed.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This bill amends the education laws as follows.
21 It updates the definition of "homeless student" to match the federal definition.
22 It updates the community school district statutes to allow for reorganization without a
23 private and special law.
24 It updates statutes regarding private schools' receipt of public funds for tuition purposes
25 to reflect the United States Supreme Court's decision in Carson v. Makin.
26 It updates statutes regarding education service centers to clarify that audits of centers
27 under the fiscal authority of a school administrative unit may be included in the financial
28 audit of that school administrative unit.
29 It clarifies that a school administrative unit's initial report to the Commissioner of
30 Education must be included as part of the unit's official audit.
31 It repeals the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 20-A, chapter 608, the School Finance Act
32 of 2003, which has been superseded by Title 20-A, chapter 606-B, the Essential Programs
33 and Services Funding Act.
